I never wanted this...⁣
⁣
But I was wrong 🤍⁣
⁣
My whole life I told myself "kids aren't for me". Growing up, I was never a "baby person" and I never pictured myself as a mother. I loved my independence and wanted to travel the world and live life to the fullest, and a baby would just get in the way.⁣
⁣
So what changed?⁣
⁣
I met my husband and although I couldn't imaging having a baby now, I also couldn't imagine my life at 60+ years old without a family. Will I still be travelling and taking photos in pretty dresses at 60? Maybe 😆 but hopefully there will be more to life than just that.⁣
⁣
So I decided to go ahead and now I wonder what I was so afraid of. This has been the most rewarding experience of my life ✨️ And we are already planning multiple trips this year (with dresses, ofc) but this time with an extra passenger 👶🏼 ⁣

A VATICAN WEDDING 🤍 

YES, it's possible and NO you don't have to be famous or pay a ton of $$$! Tips for you below: 

- only 1 person has to be Catholic but you must both complete a pre-martial Catholic counseling course 
- you do not have to be Italian or a resident of Italy
- the Vatican has specific photographers that are allowed inside
- dress code is strict - no short dresses or exposed shoulders, cleavage etc
- Yes you will walk in amongst the tourists but the actual ceremony is held inside a gated Chapel that is closed off to everyone except your wedding guests
- NO the Pope didn't marry us 😆 but you can choose your own Catholic priest (that speaks your language of choice)
- A full Catholic Mass is am option but not required 
- the Vatican can provide a singer and organist if desired
- Speaking Italian isn't necessary in order to book but it helps A LOT
- to book, just visit the Vatican Parish office and ask! We were told even 6 months in advance is enough time
- we paid less than €5,000 🤯 which included Vatican security, organist, soprano singer, and venue hire

VIP treatment for baby! 

Did you know there's virtually no added cost to travel with a baby? Most airlines and hotels give baby the royal treatment, including: 

- free ticket for baby (some airlines charge 10% of an adult ticket)
- baby gets 1 free checked bag plus a free carry-on
- checked stroller or other baby equipment usually does NOT count towards baby's baggage allowance 
- carry-on milk or other baby liquids exempt from the usual liquid allowance 
- free upgrade to a row with a baby bassinet for most longhaul flights 
- Free priority family boarding 
- Free carseats available in many airport taxis 
- Free baby crib and highchair from the hotel 

Here's to taking advantage of these perks while they're young! 🥂

✈️  Fly into Bari Airport

✈️ Fly back home from Bari Airport

My number 1 travel tip!

Whether you care about photos or not, getting up early to see the popular tourist attractions is my best tip. Places like the Trevi Fountain, Big Ben and Piazza San Marco get so crowded that they lose their appeal, especially now during high season! 

Aim to get to these major attractions early in the morning (before 8:30-9am) to enjoy them with much fewer people and more pleasant weather ☀️ Then during the day you can explore things off the beaten path (usually with less people). This is the best way to maximize your time in any given city while also enjoying it even more by avoiding most of the crowds!
